quote:
CONNECTICUT OPINION;

Meteorology Becomes a Morality Play
LEAD: I DO not know about anyone else, but I'm getting to the point where I can't take the hassle of watching the local nightly news on television. Wars, uprisings, economic roller-coaster rides, gruesome crimes - none of that stuff pushes me over the edge. All of these things have been around since Mesopotamian days and unfortunately seem likely to continue.

INVESTING;
Strategists' Latest Obsession: Cyclicals
LEAD: WALL STREET strategists, portfolio managers and analysts have a tendency to become obsessed with certain figures or industries. At various times, they have been single-minded about the money supply figures, the price of oil and, recently, the trade deficit figures.
